title: [SHOW] at Triple Rock
description: BREAKDOWN FROM TRIPLE ROCK BOOKER... we give the bands 75% ofthe door after 10.775% in taxes are taken off the top. i usually let the b ands set the door price - but typically for a monday night local act, $5 i s pretty standard - we do not charge less than $5. band members typicall y get two drink tickets a piece good for most taps and rail drinks - we do not have a backline (amps/drumset) here for bands. bands are responsibl e for bringing their own gear. we have a p.a. and microphones. we typica lly do 8pm doors with music starting 30-60 minutes after doors open. we prefer 3/4 band bills and i have typically found that one band securing the other bands on the bill works out best for draw and tone. the reason we li ke the multiple band shows is purely based on numbers. bands at this level usually have a 30 person draw, stick it on a monday night and we are cutti ng that in half unless they're friends all work in the service industry and those bands we love! let me know if you have any questions and thanks - kermit

title: Midwest CMA Award Show
description: Nominated as Americana Artist of the Year EVENT LOCATION:MEDINA ENTERTAINMENT CENTER - MAIN BALLROOM EVENT DATE: SUNDAY, FEBRUA RY 17, 2019 ARTIST ARRIVAL TIME: 3:00 PM RED CARPET: 3:30 - 4:30 P M NOMINEE VIP RECEPTION: 3:30 - 5:00 PM EVENT TIME: 5:00 - 8:00 PM  DRESS CODE The Midwest CMA Award Show is a mandatory BLACK TIE EVENT and all Nominees are expected to dress accordingly. Here are some basic gu idelines for the two dress code options. Please also ask guests that accomp any you to dress accordingly. Look sharp and show us your style. OPTION 1 - Black Tie Women * Formal (floor length) evening gown * Dressy cocktail dress * A little black dress * Dressy separates Men * Tu xedo (see Black Tie above) * Dark suit, white dress shirt, and conser vative tie * Leather dress shoes and dark dress socks OPTION 2 - Crea tive Black Tie Women * Formal (floor length) evening gown * Dressy cocktail dress * Your dressiest little black dress * Fun or unique ac cessories Men * Tuxedo/Dark Suit combined with trendy or whimsical item s, such as a black shirt or a matching colored or patterned bow tie and cu mmerbund * Unique accessories including hats and leather boots.   ** Please note that performing artists are not required to wear black tie on s tage during their performance. There will be changing rooms for artists to change attire prior to their scheduled performance time.   SEATING A s a nominee you will be given seating in the VIP section/area of the venue to ensure quick access to the stage for the winners. Below is important inf ormation regarding the ticketing / seating process: BANDS Bands that fall under the nomination categories of Best Band, Entertainer of the Year , Album of the Year and Song of the Year, etc will all be seated togethe r in VIP. Due to seating restrictions, Bands WILL NOT be granted additiona l tickets in the VIP sectionarea. However, each Band Member bands seated t ogether will receive one additional General Admission ticket to use for a g uest/spouse at no cost.  SOLO ARTISTS/INDUSTRY NOMINEES Solo artists nominated for other categories such as Vocalist of the Year, Songwriter of the Year etc., will be granted a 2 VIP tickets. plus one.  A represe ntative from the Midwest CMA will be contacting you all directly no later t han Feb 10thand will to review yourinform you which seating arrangements an d address any questions you may have. you will have. You will be asked to RSVP for yourself, your plus one and in some instances, your band member names and + one GA nameswith this representative no later than Feb. 10th or seating may not be guaranteed.  All RSVPd nominees will have assigne d seating that will be clearly marked on the VIP tables the day of the even t. We ask nominees to stay seated in their assigned seating prior to their category announcements so they are ready to accept an award on stage quick ly.  AWARD ACCEPTANCE Each artist/band is allowed thirty seconds (:30 ) for their acceptance speech once they have reached the stage and addresse d the microphone. In order to keep the event running in a smooth and timel y manner, we ask that winners make their way to the stage quickly, addres s the audience in a professional manner and exit in the time allotted. We celebrate the many views and beliefs of our member artists. Because this n ight is intended to be a positve and unifying experience for all, the boar d asks that political, relgious or other senstive issues be omitted from a ceptance speeches. Thank you. A formal timeline of the show/award order w ill be provided to all nominees prior to the event. This will allow you to keep track of your category announcement timing. We ask that all nominees are seated (if possible) at the time of their category announcement.   NOMINEE / VIP RECEPTION Nominees will all be welcome to a private nomin ee/VIP reception that will include appetizers and a champagne toast. The r eception area is private and only those who are seated in VIP may attend. You will receive a special wrist band the day of the event that will allow you entrance. The VIP/Nominee reception area opens at 3:30 pm, food and c hampagne service begins at 4:00 pm and ends promptly at 5:00 pm, immediate ly before the show.  MEDIA Nominees will be photographed by several different media outlets on the Midwest CMA red carpet. A representative o f the Midwest CMA will contact nominees individually to schedule a red-carp et appearance for media. Your scheduled time will be between 3:30 & 4:30 P M.  Additional images, video clips or .WAV files of recordings may be r equested by the production staff for the award show video and / or media ou tlets for use in show promotions or post-show reviews and write ups. All im ages taken on the red carpet will be owned and used by the Midwest CMA for public/promotional purposes. Appearance on the red carpet is implied conse nt for use of your image.  PROFESSIONAL COURTESY / CONDUCT The Midwes t CMA Award Show was founded to help support ALL original artists / songwri ters / bands and connect members of the music community together in the Mid west. While the award show is designed to honor this years elite members o f our music community, it is also designed to honor ALL our members whethe r they were nominated for an award this year or not. It is expected that all members conduct themselves appropriately at the event and show respect for the winners and performers in a gracious and professional manner. Any n ominee (or guest) who disrupts any portion of the show or displays poor sp ortsmanship at any time during the event will be asked to leave the event.  ADDITIONAL QUESTIONS / INFORMATION Direct questions that werent an swered in this letter can be sent to: board@midwestcma.org  We congratu late you on your nomination and are so excited to share this special night with you. THANK YOU for your contribution both to this night and our organ ization.     Kindest Regards,  Midwest CMA Board
